               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1r" to="38v">1r-38v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s13IHA">قران, Sixth ǧuz’ (6/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>لا يُحِبُّ اللَّهُ الْجَهْرَ بِالسُّوءِ مِنَ الْقَوْلِ إِلَّا مَنْ ظُلِمَ وَكَانَ اللَّهُ سَمِيعًا عَلِيمًا إِنْ تُبْدُوا خَيْرًا أَوْ تُخْفُوهُ أَوْ تَعْفُوا عَنْ سُوءٍ فَإِنَّ اللَّهَ كَانَ عَفُوًّا قَدِيرًا<note>4:148. The page is turned around</note>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#38v">-38v</locus>ذَلِكَ بِأَنَّ مِنْهُمْ قِسِّيسِينَ وَرُهْبَانًا وَأَنَّهُمْ لَا يَسْتَكْبِرُونَ<note>5:82</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>4:148-5:82. Some words are divided into two different lines.
The “ḏāl” is written with the dot inside. Sometimes the catchword is only the first part of the first word in the next page, sometimes there is a repeated word and the catchword is the second word of the next page. 
The name of the scribe appears in mss. 4521D (37r) and 4521X (1v, 45v). The note stating that he is actually the scribe is in 4521X (45v).  Frames in 31v-32r</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
